<div>While at DrupalCamp London 2014, I presented a session on <a href="https://drupal.org/project/df">Demo Framework</a>. It was my first time speaking at a conference and I was made to feel very welcome, so thanks to the people who attended my session and asked questions afterwards!</div>
<h3>What is Demo Framework?</h3>
<div>It’s a distribution developed by Acquia that aids the process of introducing new users to Drupal. We use it at Deeson Online to pitch Drupal to new clients.</div>
<h3>The session</h3>
<div>I kicked off by explaining some of the common problems with selling Drupal as a platform before running Demo Framework to show how it can be used in a live business environment. I also demonstrated one of our own scenarios based on an organisation with requirements for group membership. You can hear the entire presentation below.<br /> </div>
